iffpicture.lib/AllocIFFPicture                           iffpicture.lib/AllocIFFPicture

   NAME
	AllocIFFPicture -- create a new IFFPicture structure. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	picture = AllocIFFPicture()
	D0

	struct IFFPicture *AllocIFFPicture(VOID);

   FUNCTION
	Allocates and initializes a new IFFPicture structure. This function
	is the only supported way to create an IFFPicture structure since
	there are private fields that need to be initialized.

   RESULT
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure or NULL if the allocation
		  failed.

   SEE ALSO
	FreeIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/FreeIFFPicture                         iffpicture.lib/FreeIFFPicture

   NAME
	FreeIFFPicture -- deallocate an IFFPicture structure. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	FreeIFFPicture(picture);
	                  A0

	VOID FreeIFFPicture(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Deallocates all resources associated with this IFFPicture structure.
	The structure MUST have already been closed with CloseIFFPicture().
	Frees all allocated memory including BMHD, CMAP, pixel data, DEEP
	chunks (DGBL, DPEL, DLOC, DCHG, TVDC), Framestore PLTP, FAXX/GPHD
	and YUVN (YCHD) headers, metadata, CCRT cycle lists, and raw optional
	ILBM chunks (CLUT, DGVW, DYCP) when present.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure to free. This may be NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	AllocIFFPicture(), CloseIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/InitIFFPictureasDOS           iffpicture.lib/InitIFFPictureasDOS

   NAME
	InitIFFPictureasDOS -- initialize an IFFPicture as a DOS stream. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	InitIFFPictureasDOS(picture);
	                      A0

	VOID InitIFFPictureasDOS(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Initializes the IFFPicture to operate on DOS streams. Allocates and
	initializes an internal IFFHandle structure. The iff_Stream field must
	be set by the caller after calling Open() to get a BPTR file handle.

	This function follows the iffparse.library pattern where InitIFFasDOS()
	initializes the IFFHandle but does not open the file. The caller is
	responsible for opening the file and setting iff_Stream.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   SEE ALSO
	OpenIFFPicture(), GetIFFHandle(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/OpenIFFPicture                     iffpicture.lib/OpenIFFPicture

   NAME
	OpenIFFPicture -- prepare an IFFPicture to read or write a new IFF
			  stream. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = OpenIFFPicture(picture, rwMode);
	D0                      A0      D0

	LONG OpenIFFPicture(struct IFFPicture *, LONG);

   FUNCTION
	Prepares an IFFPicture to read or write a new IFF stream. The direction
	of I/O is given by rwMode (IFFF_READ or IFFF_WRITE). The IFFPicture
	must have been initialized with InitIFFPictureasDOS() and iff_Stream
	must be set to a valid BPTR file handle before calling this function.

	This function follows the iffparse.library pattern where OpenIFF()
	prepares the IFF context but does not open the file handle. The caller
	is responsible for opening the file and setting iff_Stream.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.
	rwMode  - IFFF_READ or IFFF_WRITE

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	CloseIFFPicture(), InitIFFPictureasDOS(), GetIFFHandle(),
	<iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/CloseIFFPicture                   iffpicture.lib/CloseIFFPicture

   NAME
	CloseIFFPicture -- close an IFFPicture context. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	CloseIFFPicture(picture);
	                  A0

	VOID CloseIFFPicture(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Completes an IFF read or write operation by closing the IFF context.
	The IFFHandle structure is freed. The file handle (iff_Stream) is NOT
	closed - the caller is responsible for closing it with Close(). This
	matches iffparse.library behavior where CloseIFF() doesn't close the
	file handle.

	This function can be used for cleanup if a read or write fails partway
	through.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure previously opened with
		  OpenIFFPicture(). This may be NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	OpenIFFPicture(), FreeIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ParseIFFPicture                   iffpicture.lib/ParseIFFPicture

   NAME
	ParseIFFPicture -- parse an IFF file structure. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = ParseIFFPicture(picture);
	D0                      A0

	LONG ParseIFFPicture(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Parses the IFF file structure and reads property chunks (BMHD, CMAP,
	CAMG, etc.) into the IFFPicture structure. Must be called after
	OpenIFFPicture(). This function uses iffparse.library's ParseIFF() to
	traverse the file and store property chunks that were declared with
	PropChunk(). For FORM ILBM, PBM, and ACBM, optional PCHG, SHAM, and
	CTBL multipalette chunks are read and stored when present (SHAM takes
	precedence over PCHG when both exist). For FORM ILBM, optional DGVW,
	CLUT, and DYCP property chunks are registered and read when present;
	all CCRT (Graphicraft colour-cycle timing) instances are collected.

	If the stream begins with FORM CAT or FORM LIST, parsing steps through
	the container until the first supported picture FORM (ILBM, PBM, RGBN,
	RGB8, DEEP, ACBM, FAXX, YUVN, etc.) is found. One image is loaded per
	successful parse cycle; remaining FORMs in the container are not
	exported by iff2png in a single run.

	Supports FORM ILBM (including 24-bit, optional 32-plane and greyscale
	paths, NewTek Digi-View 21-plane RGB when BMHD matches, Video Toaster
	Framestore 16-plane + PLTP), PBM, RGBN, RGB8, FORM DEEP (DGBL, DPEL,
	DLOC, DBOD, DCHG, TVDC), ACBM, FORM FAXX (FXHD, PAGE, GPHD), and FORM
	YUVN (YCHD, DATY, DATU, DATV). For Framestore detection, PLTP is read
	when present in ILBM; isFramestore is set when nPlanes=16 and PLTP
	maps to components 6 and 7. For Digi-View-style RGB ILBM, isDigiViewRgb
	is set when nPlanes==21 on the Digi-View body path and/or a DGVW chunk
	is present (see IsDigiViewRgb()).

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	OpenIFFPicture(), ReadBMHD(), ReadCMAP(), ReadCAMG(),
	GetMultipaletteChunkId(), Decode(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadBMHD                             iffpicture.lib/ReadBMHD

   NAME
	ReadBMHD -- read BMHD (Bitmap Header) chunk. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = ReadBMHD(picture);
	D0                A0

	LONG ReadBMHD(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the BMHD (Bitmap Header) chunk and stores it in the IFFPicture
	structure. This chunk contains image dimensions, bitplane count,
	compression type, masking, and other metadata. Uses iffparse.library's
	FindProp() to locate the stored property chunk that was declared with
	PropChunk() during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), GetBMHD(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadCMAP                             iffpicture.lib/ReadCMAP

   NAME
	ReadCMAP -- read CMAP (Color Map) chunk. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = ReadCMAP(picture);
	D0                A0

	LONG ReadCMAP(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the CMAP (Color Map) chunk containing palette data. The palette
	consists of RGB triplets (r, g, b, r, g, b, ...). For 4-bit palettes,
	colors are automatically scaled to 8-bit. Uses iffparse.library's
	FindProp() to locate the stored property chunk that was declared with
	PropChunk() during ParseIFFPicture().

	CMAP is optional for some formats (e.g., DEEP, RGBN, RGB8). If the
	chunk is not present, this function returns successfully without
	setting an error.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), GetIFFColorMap(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadCAMG                             iffpicture.lib/ReadCAMG

   NAME
	ReadCAMG -- read CAMG (Amiga Viewport Modes) chunk. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = ReadCAMG(picture);
	D0                A0

	LONG ReadCAMG(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the CAMG (Amiga Viewport Modes) chunk containing display mode
	flags such as HAM, EHB, LACE, HIRES, etc. Uses iffparse.library's
	FindProp() to locate the stored property chunk that was declared with
	PropChunk() during ParseIFFPicture().

	CAMG is optional. If the chunk is not present, this function returns
	successfully and GetVPModes() will return 0.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), GetVPModes(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadBODY                             iffpicture.lib/ReadBODY

   NAME
	ReadBODY -- read BODY chunk header information. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = ReadBODY(picture);
	D0                A0

	LONG ReadBODY(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the BODY chunk header information. The BODY chunk contains the
	actual image pixel data. This function stores the chunk size and
	position for later reading during decoding.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), Decode(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadABIT                             iffpicture.lib/ReadABIT

   NAME
	ReadABIT -- read ABIT (Alpha Bitmap) chunk header information. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = ReadABIT(picture);
	D0                 A0

	LONG ReadABIT(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the ABIT (Alpha Bitmap) chunk header information. Similar to
	ReadBODY() but for alpha channel data in ACBM format images.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), Decode(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetIFFHandle                       iffpicture.lib/GetIFFHandle

   NAME
	GetIFFHandle -- get pointer to internal IFFHandle structure. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	iff = GetIFFHandle(picture);
	D0                 A0

	struct IFFHandle *GetIFFHandle(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the internal IFFHandle structure. This allows the
	caller to set iff_Stream after calling InitIFFPictureasDOS() and before
	calling OpenIFFPicture(). Returns NULL if the IFFPicture is not
	initialized.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	iff - pointer to IFFHandle structure or NULL if not initialized.

   SEE ALSO
	InitIFFPictureasDOS(), OpenIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetWidth                             iffpicture.lib/GetWidth

   NAME
	GetWidth -- get image width in pixels. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	width = GetWidth(picture);
	D0              A0

	UWORD GetWidth(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the image width in pixels. For ILBM/PBM/RGBN/RGB8/ACBM/FAXX
	uses BMHD or FXHD; for DEEP uses DGBL DisplayWidth; for YUVN uses
	YCHD. Return 0 if no header is loaded.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	width - image width in pixels, or 0 if not loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	GetHeight(), GetDepth(), GetBMHD(), GetFXHD(), GetYCHD(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetHeight                           iffpicture.lib/GetHeight

   NAME
	GetHeight -- get image height in pixels. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	height = GetHeight(picture);
	D0                A0

	UWORD GetHeight(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the image height in pixels. For ILBM/PBM/RGBN/RGB8/ACBM/FAXX
	uses BMHD or FXHD; for DEEP uses DGBL DisplayHeight; for YUVN uses
	YCHD. Return 0 if no header is loaded.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	height - image height in pixels, or 0 if not loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	GetWidth(), GetDepth(), GetBMHD(), GetFXHD(), GetYCHD(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetDepth                             iffpicture.lib/GetDepth

   NAME
	GetDepth -- get number of bitplanes. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	depth = GetDepth(picture);
	D0               A0

	UWORD GetDepth(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the number of bitplanes (or effective depth). For ILBM/PBM/
	RGBN/RGB8/ACBM uses BMHD nPlanes; for DEEP derived from DPEL element
	depths; for YUVN/FAXX returns 0 or format-specific depth. Return 0 if
	not applicable or no header loaded.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	depth - number of bitplanes or effective depth, or 0 if not loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	GetWidth(), GetHeight(), GetBMHD(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetFormType                         iffpicture.lib/GetFormType

   NAME
	GetFormType -- get IFF FORM type identifier. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	type = GetFormType(picture);
	D0                A0

	ULONG GetFormType(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the IFF FORM type identifier (e.g., ID_ILBM, ID_PBM, ID_DEEP,
	ID_YUVN, ID_FAXX). This identifies the image format variant. Note:
	Video Toaster Framestore files use ID_ILBM with 16 planes and a PLTP
	chunk; use IsFramestore() to detect this variant.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	type - IFF FORM type identifier, or 0 if not loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	<iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetVPModes                           iffpicture.lib/GetVPModes

   NAME
	GetVPModes -- get Amiga viewport mode flags from CAMG chunk. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	modes = GetVPModes(picture);
	D0                 A0

	ULONG GetVPModes(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the Amiga viewport mode flags from the CAMG chunk. The returned
	ULONG contains flags such as vmHAM, vmEXTRA_HALFBRITE, vmLACE, vmHIRES,
	etc. Returns 0 if CAMG chunk is not present. This is the raw CAMG value
	that can be used with BestPictureModeID() or for direct mode matching.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	modes - viewport mode flags, or 0 if CAMG not present.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCAMG(), BestPictureModeID(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetFAXXCompression             iffpicture.lib/GetFAXXCompression

   NAME
	GetFAXXCompression -- get FAXX compression type. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	compression = GetFAXXCompression(picture);
	D0                            A0

	UBYTE GetFAXXCompression(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the compression type used in FAXX format images. Only valid
	for images with form type ID_FAXX. Returns 0 if not a FAXX image or
	if compression information is not available.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	compression - Compression type:
		      0 = None
		      1 = Modified Huffman (MH)
		      2 = Modified READ (MR)
		      4 = Modified Modified READ (MMR)

   SEE ALSO
	GetFormType(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetBMHD                               iffpicture.lib/GetBMHD

   NAME
	GetBMHD -- get pointer to BitMapHeader structure. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	bmhd = GetBMHD(picture);
	D0                A0

	struct BitMapHeader *GetBMHD(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the internal BMHD (Bitmap Header) structure. This
	pointer remains valid until the IFFPicture is freed. Returns NULL if
	not loaded.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	bmhd - pointer to BitMapHeader structure, or NULL if not loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadBMHD(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetFXHD                               iffpicture.lib/GetFXHD

   NAME
	GetFXHD -- get pointer to FAXX header (FXHD chunk). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	fxhd = GetFXHD(picture);
	D0                A0

	struct FaxHeader *GetFXHD(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the internal FaxHeader structure (FXHD chunk).
	Only valid for images with form type ID_FAXX. Contains Width, Height,
	LineLength, VRes, and Compression (MH, MR, MMR). The pointer remains
	valid until the IFFPicture is freed. Returns NULL if not FAXX or not
	loaded.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	fxhd - pointer to FaxHeader structure, or NULL if not FAXX or not
	       loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	GetFormType(), GetGPHD(), GetFAXXCompression(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetGPHD                               iffpicture.lib/GetGPHD

   NAME
	GetGPHD -- get pointer to GPHD header (optional FAXX extension). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	gphd = GetGPHD(picture);
	D0                 A0

	struct GPHDHeader *GetGPHD(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the internal GPHDHeader structure when present
	in a FAXX file (e.g. GPSoftware extension). Optional; many FAXX
	files have only FXHD. The pointer remains valid until the IFFPicture
	is freed. Returns NULL if not present.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	gphd - pointer to GPHDHeader structure, or NULL if not present.

   SEE ALSO
	GetFXHD(), GetFormType(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetYCHD                               iffpicture.lib/GetYCHD

   NAME
	GetYCHD -- get pointer to YUVN header (YCHD chunk). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	ychd = GetYCHD(picture);
	D0                 A0

	struct YCHDHeader *GetYCHD(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the internal YCHDHeader structure (YCHD chunk).
	Only valid for images with form type ID_YUVN (MacroSystem VLab YUV
	format). Contains dimensions, aspect, compression, Mode (400/411/422/
	444, etc.), and Norm (PAL/NTSC). The pointer remains valid until the
	IFFPicture is freed. Returns NULL if not YUVN or not loaded.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	ychd - pointer to YCHDHeader structure, or NULL if not YUVN or not
	       loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	GetFormType(), GetWidth(), GetHeight(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetIFFColorMap                     iffpicture.lib/GetIFFColorMap

   NAME
	GetIFFColorMap -- get pointer to IFFColorMap structure. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	cmap = GetIFFColorMap(picture);
	D0                  A0

	struct IFFColorMap *GetIFFColorMap(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the internal IFFColorMap structure (palette data).
	This pointer remains valid until the IFFPicture is freed. Returns NULL
	if not loaded.

	Note: Renamed from GetColorMap to avoid conflict with graphics.library
	function.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	cmap - pointer to IFFColorMap structure, or NULL if not loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCMAP(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetPixelData                         iffpicture.lib/GetPixelData

   NAME
	GetPixelData -- get pointer to decoded pixel data buffer. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	data = GetPixelData(picture);
	D0                 A0

	UBYTE *GetPixelData(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the decoded pixel data buffer. The data format
	depends on the image type (RGB, indexed, etc.). Returns NULL if image
	has not been decoded.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	data - pointer to pixel data buffer, or NULL if not decoded.

   SEE ALSO
	Decode(), DecodeToRGB(), GetPixelDataSize(), GetImageInfo(),
	GetPaletteIndices(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetPixelDataSize                   iffpicture.lib/GetPixelDataSize

   NAME
	GetPixelDataSize -- get size of decoded pixel data in bytes. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	size = GetPixelDataSize(picture);
	D0                    A0

	ULONG GetPixelDataSize(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the size in bytes of the decoded pixel data. This is useful for
	calculating buffer sizes.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	size - size in bytes of pixel data, or 0 if not decoded.

   SEE ALSO
	GetPixelData(), Decode(), GetImageInfo(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetImageInfo                           iffpicture.lib/GetImageInfo

   NAME
	GetImageInfo -- get aggregate of core image properties. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	info = GetImageInfo(picture);
	D0                  A0

	struct IFFImageInfo *GetImageInfo(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to an IFFImageInfo structure containing all core
	image properties in one place: width, height, depth, formType,
	viewportModes, compressedSize, decodedSize, hasAlpha, isHAM, isEHB,
	isFramestore, isDigiViewRgb, isCompressed, multipaletteChunkId,
	isIndexed, isGrayscale, isLoaded, isDecoded. The multipaletteChunkId
	field matches GetMultipaletteChunkId() (IFF chunk ID or 0). Useful to
	avoid multiple getter calls. The structure is allocated statically and
	remains valid until the next GetImageInfo() call or until the
	IFFPicture is freed. Returns NULL if the picture is invalid or not
	loaded.

	isFramestore is TRUE for NewTek Video Toaster framestore (ILBM with
	16 planes and PLTP mapping to components 6 and 7). isDigiViewRgb
	matches IsDigiViewRgb() (Digi-View RGB ILBM body and/or DGVW chunk).

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	info - pointer to IFFImageInfo structure, or NULL if invalid/not
	       loaded.

   SEE ALSO
	GetWidth(), GetHeight(), GetFormType(), IsFramestore(), IsDigiViewRgb(),
	HasAlpha(), GetMultipaletteChunkId(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/HasAlpha                             iffpicture.lib/HasAlpha

   NAME
	HasAlpha -- check if image has alpha channel. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	hasAlpha = HasAlpha(picture);
	D0                    A0

	BOOL HasAlpha(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns TRUE if the image has an alpha channel. This is determined
	during format analysis.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	hasAlpha - TRUE if image has alpha channel, FALSE otherwise.

   SEE ALSO
	AnalyzeFormat(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IsHAM                                 iffpicture.lib/IsHAM

   NAME
	IsHAM -- check if image uses HAM mode. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	isHAM = IsHAM(picture);
	D0              A0

	BOOL IsHAM(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns TRUE if the image uses HAM (Hold And Modify) mode. This is
	determined from the CAMG chunk or during format analysis.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	isHAM - TRUE if image uses HAM mode, FALSE otherwise.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCAMG(), AnalyzeFormat(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IsEHB                                 iffpicture.lib/IsEHB

   NAME
	IsEHB -- check if image uses EHB mode. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	isEHB = IsEHB(picture);
	D0              A0

	BOOL IsEHB(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns TRUE if the image uses EHB (Extra Half Brite) mode. This is
	determined from the CAMG chunk or during format analysis.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	isEHB - TRUE if image uses EHB mode, FALSE otherwise.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCAMG(), AnalyzeFormat(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IsFramestore                         iffpicture.lib/IsFramestore

   NAME
	IsFramestore -- check if image is NewTek Video Toaster framestore. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	isFS = IsFramestore(picture);
	D0                    A0

	BOOL IsFramestore(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns TRUE if the image is a NewTek Video Toaster framestore: FORM
	ILBM with 16 bitplanes and a PLTP chunk that maps planes 0-7 to
	component 6 and planes 8-15 to component 7 (quadrature Y/C encoding).
	Such files are decoded via a dedicated path (luma/chroma demodulation
	and BT.601 to RGB). Returns FALSE for standard ILBM or other formats.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	isFS - TRUE if Video Toaster framestore, FALSE otherwise.

   SEE ALSO
	GetFormType(), GetImageInfo(), Decode(), IsDigiViewRgb(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IsDigiViewRgb                       iffpicture.lib/IsDigiViewRgb

   NAME
	IsDigiViewRgb -- check for NewTek Digi-View RGB ILBM. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	isDv = IsDigiViewRgb(picture);
	D0                    A0

	BOOL IsDigiViewRgb(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns TRUE when the picture is treated as Digi-View RGB: typically
	FORM ILBM with a 21-plane interleaved body decoded on the Digi-View
	path, and/or when a DGVW property chunk is present (tooling flag even
	if plane count differs). Use GetImageInfo()->isDigiViewRgb for the
	same boolean without a separate call.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	isDv - TRUE if Digi-View RGB detection applies, FALSE otherwise.

   SEE ALSO
	GetImageInfo(), ParseIFFPicture(), Decode(), ReadDGVW(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IsCompressed                         iffpicture.lib/IsCompressed

   NAME
	IsCompressed -- check if image data is compressed. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	isCompressed = IsCompressed(picture);
	D0                      A0

	BOOL IsCompressed(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns TRUE if the image data is compressed. This is determined from
	the format header (BMHD, DGBL, FXHD, etc.) during format analysis.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	isCompressed - TRUE if image is compressed, FALSE otherwise.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadBMHD(), AnalyzeFormat(), GetMultipaletteChunkId(),
	<iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetMultipaletteChunkId    iffpicture.lib/GetMultipaletteChunkId

   NAME
	GetMultipaletteChunkId -- multipalette source chunk ID. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	id = GetMultipaletteChunkId(picture);
	D0                              A0

	ULONG GetMultipaletteChunkId(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	After the picture has been loaded (DecodePicture / parse path has run
	ReadILBMMultipalette for ILBM, PBM, and ACBM), returns the IFF chunk ID
	of the multipalette source that drives per-row palette during indexed
	decode: MAKE_ID('S','H','A','M'), MAKE_ID('P','C','H','G'), or
	MAKE_ID('C','T','B','L'), or 0 if none. Precedence matches decode:
	SHAM over PCHG over CTBL. Compare the result with MAKE_ID(); do not
	rely on numeric constants across library versions.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	id - multipalette chunk ID, or 0.

   SEE ALSO
	IsMultipaletteActive(), GetImageInfo(), ParseIFFPicture(),
	Decode(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IsMultipaletteActive      iffpicture.lib/IsMultipaletteActive

   NAME
	IsMultipaletteActive -- TRUE if multipalette decode applies. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	active = IsMultipaletteActive(picture);
	D0                                A0

	BOOL IsMultipaletteActive(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns TRUE if GetMultipaletteChunkId() would return a
	non-zero chunk ID (SHAM, PCHG, or CTBL is active for decode).

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	active - TRUE or FALSE.

   SEE ALSO
	GetMultipaletteChunkId(), GetImageInfo(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetPaletteIndices           iffpicture.lib/GetPaletteIndices

   NAME
	GetPaletteIndices -- pointer to decoded palette indices. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	indices = GetPaletteIndices(picture);
	D0                           A0

	UBYTE *GetPaletteIndices(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	After Decode(), returns a pointer to width*height bytes of original
	palette indices (one per pixel), or NULL if not present. Memory is
	library-owned; valid until FreeIFFPicture(). Not all decode paths
	produce indices; multipalette true-colour output may omit this buffer.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	indices - pointer to index buffer, or NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	GetPixelData(), Decode(), IsMultipaletteActive(),
	<iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/Decode                                 iffpicture.lib/Decode

   NAME
	Decode -- decode IFF image data to internal format. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = Decode(picture);
	D0              A0

	LONG Decode(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Decodes the IFF image data into an internal format suitable for further
	processing. Handles all IFF formats (ILBM, PBM, RGBN, RGB8, DEEP,
	ACBM, FAXX, YUVN) and compression methods (ByteRun1 including
	column-wise packing and repeat count 128 compatibility, DEEP RUNLENGTH/
	TVDC, Modified Huffman, Modified READ, etc.). ILBM paths include HAM,
	EHB, multipalette (PCHG, SHAM, CTBL) on applicable indexed paths,
	24-bit and 32-plane RGBA-style output, greyscale without CMAP, NewTek
	Digi-View 21-plane RGB interleaved bodies, DEST merge remapping when
	DEST is present, BMHD mask plane and transparent colour and lasso-style
	masking, and Video Toaster Framestore (16-plane ILBM + PLTP,
	quadrature Y/C to RGB). Must be called after ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), DecodeToRGB(), DecodeToBitMap(),
	GetMultipaletteChunkId(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/DecodeToRGB                         iffpicture.lib/DecodeToRGB

   NAME
	DecodeToRGB -- decode IFF image and convert to RGB format. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = DecodeToRGB(picture, rgbData, size);
	D0                      A0      A1      A2

	LONG DecodeToRGB(struct IFFPicture *, UBYTE **, ULONG *);

   FUNCTION
	Decodes the IFF image and converts it to RGB format. Allocates a buffer
	containing 24-bit RGB data (r, g, b, r, g, b, ...) suitable for writing
	to PNG or other RGB-based formats. The caller is responsible for
	freeing the returned buffer.

	Note: The returned rgbData may point to picture->pixelData, which is
	freed by FreeIFFPicture(). Do not free it separately.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.
	rgbData - pointer to variable to receive RGB data pointer.
	size    - pointer to variable to receive data size in bytes.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	Decode(), FreeIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/DecodeToBitMap                     iffpicture.lib/DecodeToBitMap

   NAME
	DecodeToBitMap -- create Amiga BitMap from decoded IFF image. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	bitmap = DecodeToBitMap(picture, modeID, friendBitmap);
	D0                      A0      D0      A1

	struct BitMap *DecodeToBitMap(struct IFFPicture *, ULONG,
	                               struct BitMap *);

   FUNCTION
	Decodes the IFF image and creates an Amiga BitMap structure ready for
	display. The BitMap is allocated using AllocBitMap() with the
	specified modeID. Supports both planar (bitplane) and chunky (8-bit per
	pixel) display modes.

	For planar modes: Converts RGB data directly to bitplanes.

	For chunky modes: Uses WriteChunkyPixels() if available (V40+),
	otherwise falls back to direct conversion.

	The caller is responsible for freeing the BitMap using FreeBitMap()
	when no longer needed.

   INPUTS
	picture     - IFFPicture structure (must be decoded).
	modeID      - Display mode ID (use BestPictureModeID() to find).
	friendBitmap - Optional friend bitmap for efficient allocation
		       (NULL if not needed).

   RESULT
	bitmap - pointer to allocated BitMap, or NULL on failure.

   SEE ALSO
	Decode(), BestPictureModeID(), FreeBitMap(), DecodeToRastPort(),
	<iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/DecodeToRastPort                 iffpicture.lib/DecodeToRastPort

   NAME
	DecodeToRastPort -- create off-screen RastPort with BitMap from decoded
			    IFF image. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	rp = DecodeToRastPort(picture, modeID, friendBitmap);
	D0                      A0      D0      A1

	struct RastPort *DecodeToRastPort(struct IFFPicture *, ULONG,
	                                  struct BitMap *);

   FUNCTION
	Decodes the IFF image and creates an off-screen RastPort with attached
	BitMap. This is a convenience function that calls DecodeToBitMap() and
	then initializes a RastPort.

	The RastPort is allocated and initialized with InitRastPort(). The
	BitMap is attached and ready for rendering operations.

	The caller is responsible for freeing the RastPort using FreeRastPort()
	when no longer needed. This will also free the attached BitMap.

   INPUTS
	picture     - IFFPicture structure (must be decoded).
	modeID      - Display mode ID (use BestPictureModeID() to find).
	friendBitmap - Optional friend bitmap for efficient allocation
		       (NULL if not needed).

   RESULT
	rp - pointer to allocated RastPort, or NULL on failure.

   SEE ALSO
	Decode(), DecodeToBitMap(), FreeRastPort(), BestPictureModeID(),
	<iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/FreeRastPort                         iffpicture.lib/FreeRastPort

   NAME
	FreeRastPort -- free RastPort and its attached BitMap. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	FreeRastPort(rp);
	              A0

	VOID FreeRastPort(struct RastPort *);

   FUNCTION
	Frees a RastPort and its attached BitMap created by DecodeToRastPort().
	This function properly cleans up both the RastPort structure and the
	BitMap memory.

   INPUTS
	rp - RastPort to free (must have been created by DecodeToRastPort()).
	     This may be NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	DecodeToRastPort(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/AnalyzeFormat                       iffpicture.lib/AnalyzeFormat

   NAME
	AnalyzeFormat -- analyze IFF image format and properties. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = AnalyzeFormat(picture);
	D0                    A0

	LONG AnalyzeFormat(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Analyzes the loaded IFF image to determine its properties such as
	color type (indexed, grayscale, RGB), special modes (HAM, EHB,
	Framestore), DEEP/YUVN pixel elements, compression, and alpha
	channel presence. This information is used to optimize PNG encoding.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture() and before decoding. This
	function is optional - Decode() will work without it, but it is needed
	for GetOptimalPNGConfig().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), GetOptimalPNGConfig(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/GetOptimalPNGConfig           iffpicture.lib/GetOptimalPNGConfig

   NAME
	GetOptimalPNGConfig -- determine optimal PNG encoding configuration.
			       (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = GetOptimalPNGConfig(picture, config, opaque);
	D0                          A0      A1      D0

	LONG GetOptimalPNGConfig(struct IFFPicture *, struct PNGConfig *, BOOL);

   FUNCTION
	Determines the optimal PNG encoding configuration for the IFF image.
	This includes color type, bit depth, palette (if indexed), and
	transparency settings. Supports ILBM (including Framestore), PBM,
	DEEP, RGBN, RGB8, ACBM, FAXX, and YUVN. The configuration is stored
	in the provided PNGConfig structure. The caller is responsible for
	freeing any allocated palette or transparency data using
	PNGEncoder_FreeConfig().

	The opaque parameter controls transparency handling:
	- If FALSE (default): Honors transparentColor from BMHD when
	  masking == mskHasTransparentColor, including index 0 (per ILBM
	  specification).
	- If TRUE: Skips transparency for index 0 to keep black visible
	  (legacy behavior).

	Must be called after AnalyzeFormat() and before DecodeToRGB().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.
	config  - pointer to PNGConfig structure to fill.
	opaque  - If TRUE, skip transparency for color index 0 (legacy behavior).
		  If FALSE, honor ILBM specification including transparent index 0.

   RESULT
	error - 0 if successful or an IFFPICTURE_#? error code if unsuccessful.

   SEE ALSO
	AnalyzeFormat(), DecodeToRGB(), PNGEncoder_FreeConfig(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/BestPictureModeID             iffpicture.lib/BestPictureModeID

   NAME
	BestPictureModeID -- determine best Amiga screenmode for displaying
			     IFF image. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	modeID = BestPictureModeID(picture, sourceViewPort, sourceModeID,
				   monitorID);
	D0                      A0      A1              D0          D1

	ULONG BestPictureModeID(struct IFFPicture *, struct ViewPort *,
				ULONG, ULONG);

   FUNCTION
	Determines the best Amiga screenmode for displaying the IFF image. Uses
	graphics.library BestModeIDA() to find a ModeID that matches the image
	properties.

	If a CAMG chunk is present, it uses those viewport mode flags (HAM,
	EHB, LACE, HIRES) as requirements. If no CAMG chunk exists, it infers
	requirements from the image properties (width, height, depth). For
	DEEP and YUVN, dimensions come from DGBL or YCHD respectively.
	Framestore (IsFramestore()) uses BMHD dimensions.

	The function verifies that the recommended mode is actually available
	using ModeNotAvailable() before returning it to the caller.

   INPUTS
	picture       - pointer to IFFPicture structure (must be parsed).
	sourceViewPort - Optional ViewPort to match monitor type (NULL if not
			 used).
	sourceModeID  - Optional ModeID to use as source (0 if not used,
			overrides ViewPort).
	monitorID     - Optional monitor ID to restrict search (0 if not used).

   RESULT
	modeID - Best matching ModeID, or INVALID_ID if no match found or mode
		 is not available.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), GetVPModes(), DecodeToBitMap(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IFFPictureError                    iffpicture.lib/IFFPictureError

   NAME
	IFFPictureError -- get last error code. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	error = IFFPictureError(picture);
	D0                    A0

	LONG IFFPictureError(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the last error code that occurred during an IFFPicture
	operation. Error codes are negative values (IFFPICTURE_* constants) or
	0 for success.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	error - error code (IFFPICTURE_* constant) or 0 for success.

   SEE ALSO
	IFFPictureErrorString(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/IFFPictureErrorString              iffpicture.lib/IFFPictureErrorString

   NAME
	IFFPictureErrorString -- get last error message. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	message = IFFPictureErrorString(picture);
	D0                         A0

	const char *IFFPictureErrorString(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to a null-terminated string describing the last error.
	The string is stored in the IFFPicture structure and remains valid
	until the next operation or until the IFFPicture is freed.

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	message - pointer to error message string, or "Invalid picture object"
		  if picture is NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	IFFPictureError(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadGRAB                             iffpicture.lib/ReadGRAB

   NAME
	ReadGRAB -- read GRAB chunk (hotspot coordinates). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	grab = ReadGRAB(picture);
	D0                A0

	struct Point2D *ReadGRAB(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the GRAB chunk containing hotspot coordinates for the image.
	Returns a pointer to a Point2D structure in IFFPicture's memory, or
	NULL if not found. The pointer is valid until FreeIFFPicture() is
	called. Library owns the memory - caller must NOT free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	grab - pointer to Point2D structure containing hotspot coordinates,
	       or NULL if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadDEST                             iffpicture.lib/ReadDEST

   NAME
	ReadDEST -- read DEST chunk (destination merge information). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	dest = ReadDEST(picture);
	D0                A0

	struct DestMerge *ReadDEST(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the DEST chunk containing destination merge information for
	bitplane operations. Returns a pointer to a DestMerge structure in
	IFFPicture's memory, or NULL if not found. The pointer is valid until
	FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library owns the memory - caller must NOT
	free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	dest - pointer to DestMerge structure, or NULL if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadSPRT                             iffpicture.lib/ReadSPRT

   NAME
	ReadSPRT -- read SPRT chunk (sprite precedence). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	precedence = ReadSPRT(picture);
	D0                  A0

	UWORD *ReadSPRT(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the SPRT chunk containing sprite precedence value. Returns a
	pointer to a UWORD in IFFPicture's memory containing the precedence
	value, or NULL if not found. Precedence 0 is the highest (foremost).
	The pointer is valid until FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library owns
	the memory - caller must NOT free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	precedence - pointer to UWORD containing precedence value, or NULL
		     if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadCRNG                             iffpicture.lib/ReadCRNG

   NAME
	ReadCRNG -- read CRNG chunk (color range, first instance). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	crng = ReadCRNG(picture);
	D0                A0

	struct CRange *ReadCRNG(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the first CRNG chunk containing color range information for
	color cycling. Returns a pointer to a CRange structure in
	IFFPicture's memory, or NULL if not found. Multiple CRNG chunks can
	exist; this returns the first one. The pointer is valid until
	FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library owns the memory - caller must NOT
	free.

	To get all CRNG chunks, use ReadAllCRNG().

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	crng - pointer to CRange structure, or NULL if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadAllCRNG(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadAllCRNG                       iffpicture.lib/ReadAllCRNG

   NAME
	ReadAllCRNG -- read all CRNG chunks (color ranges). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	crngList = ReadAllCRNG(picture);
	D0                    A0

	struct CRangeList *ReadAllCRNG(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads all CRNG chunks containing color range information. Returns a
	pointer to a CRangeList structure containing count and array pointer
	into IFFPicture's memory, or NULL if not found. Pointers are valid
	until FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library owns the memory - caller
	must NOT free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	crngList - pointer to CRangeList structure containing count and
		   ranges array, or NULL if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCRNG(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadCCRT                             iffpicture.lib/ReadCCRT

   NAME
	ReadCCRT -- read CCRT chunk (Graphicraft colour-cycle timing, first). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	ccrt = ReadCCRT(picture);
	D0                A0

	struct CycleInfo *ReadCCRT(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the first CCRT (Graphicraft) colour-cycle timing
	record stored during parse, or NULL if none. CCRT complements CRNG with
	interval timing (seconds/microseconds). Library-owned memory; valid
	until FreeIFFPicture(). For every CCRT instance, use ReadAllCCRT().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	ccrt - pointer to CycleInfo, or NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadAllCCRT(), ParseIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadAllCCRT                       iffpicture.lib/ReadAllCCRT

   NAME
	ReadAllCCRT -- read all CCRT chunks. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	list = ReadAllCCRT(picture);
	D0                  A0

	struct CycleInfoList *ReadAllCCRT(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a CycleInfoList (count + items array) for all CCRT chunks
	collected during ParseIFFPicture(), or NULL if none. Library-owned;
	valid until FreeIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	list - pointer to CycleInfoList, or NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCCRT(), ParseIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadCLUT                             iffpicture.lib/ReadCLUT

   NAME
	ReadCLUT -- read CLUT chunk (raw payload). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	data = ReadCLUT(picture, sizeOut);
	D0                A0      A1

	UBYTE *ReadCLUT(struct IFFPicture *, ULONG *sizeOut);

   FUNCTION
	Returns a pointer to the raw CLUT chunk body and sets *sizeOut to the
	byte length, or NULL / 0 if absent. Stored for host tools; decode does
	not yet drive deep ILBM colour solely from CLUT. Library-owned until
	FreeIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.
	sizeOut - pointer to ULONG to receive payload size (may be NULL to
		  ignore size if the return value is sufficient).

   RESULT
	data - pointer to CLUT bytes, or NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadDYCP(), ReadDGVW(), ParseIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadDGVW                             iffpicture.lib/ReadDGVW

   NAME
	ReadDGVW -- read DGVW chunk (Digi-View, raw payload). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	data = ReadDGVW(picture, sizeOut);
	D0                A0      A1

	UBYTE *ReadDGVW(struct IFFPicture *, ULONG *sizeOut);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the raw DGVW property chunk body and sets *sizeOut, or NULL.
	Presence contributes to IsDigiViewRgb() for tooling. Library-owned
	until FreeIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.
	sizeOut - pointer to ULONG for payload size, or NULL.

   RESULT
	data - pointer to DGVW bytes, or NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	IsDigiViewRgb(), ReadCLUT(), ParseIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadDYCP                             iffpicture.lib/ReadDYCP

   NAME
	ReadDYCP -- read DYCP chunk (dynamic palette, raw payload). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	data = ReadDYCP(picture, sizeOut);
	D0                A0      A1

	UBYTE *ReadDYCP(struct IFFPicture *, ULONG *sizeOut);

   FUNCTION
	Returns the raw DYCP chunk body and sets *sizeOut, or NULL. Payload
	is stored for tools; raster decode does not simulate dynamic HAM /
	hardware palette behaviour from DYCP yet. Library-owned until
	FreeIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.
	sizeOut - pointer to ULONG for payload size, or NULL.

   RESULT
	data - pointer to DYCP bytes, or NULL.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCLUT(), ParseIFFPicture(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadCopyright                     iffpicture.lib/ReadCopyright

   NAME
	ReadCopyright -- read Copyright chunk. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	copyright = ReadCopyright(picture);
	D0                      A0

	STRPTR ReadCopyright(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the Copyright chunk containing copyright text. Returns a
	pointer to a null-terminated string in IFFPicture's memory, or NULL
	if not found. The pointer is valid until FreeIFFPicture() is called.
	Library owns the memory - caller must NOT free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	copyright - pointer to null-terminated copyright string, or NULL if
		    not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadAuthor(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadAuthor                           iffpicture.lib/ReadAuthor

   NAME
	ReadAuthor -- read AUTH chunk (author information). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	author = ReadAuthor(picture);
	D0                A0

	STRPTR ReadAuthor(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the AUTH chunk containing author information. Returns a pointer
	to a null-terminated string in IFFPicture's memory, or NULL if not
	found. The pointer is valid until FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library
	owns the memory - caller must NOT free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	author - pointer to null-terminated author string, or NULL if not
		 found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadCopyright(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadAnnotation                     iffpicture.lib/ReadAnnotation

   NAME
	ReadAnnotation -- read ANNO chunk (first instance). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	annotation = ReadAnnotation(picture);
	D0                      A0

	STRPTR ReadAnnotation(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the first ANNO chunk containing annotation text. Returns a
	pointer to a null-terminated string in IFFPicture's memory, or NULL
	if not found. Multiple ANNO chunks can exist; this returns the first
	one. The pointer is valid until FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library
	owns the memory - caller must NOT free.

	To get all ANNO chunks, use ReadAllAnnotations().

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	annotation - pointer to null-terminated annotation string, or NULL if
		     not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadAllAnnotations(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadAllAnnotations           iffpicture.lib/ReadAllAnnotations

   NAME
	ReadAllAnnotations -- read all ANNO chunks (annotations). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	textList = ReadAllAnnotations(picture);
	D0                        A0

	struct TextList *ReadAllAnnotations(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads all ANNO chunks containing annotation text. Returns a pointer
	to a TextList structure containing count and array pointer into
	IFFPicture's memory, or NULL if not found. Pointers are valid until
	FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library owns the memory - caller must
	NOT free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	textList - pointer to TextList structure containing count and texts
		   array, or NULL if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadAnnotation(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadText                             iffpicture.lib/ReadText

   NAME
	ReadText -- read TEXT chunk (first instance). (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	text = ReadText(picture);
	D0              A0

	STRPTR ReadText(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads the first TEXT chunk containing text data. Returns a pointer
	to a null-terminated string in IFFPicture's memory, or NULL if not
	found. Multiple TEXT chunks can exist; this returns the first one.
	The pointer is valid until FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library owns
	the memory - caller must NOT free.

	To get all TEXT chunks, use ReadAllTexts().

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	text - pointer to null-terminated text string, or NULL if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadAllTexts(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

iffpicture.lib/ReadAllTexts                       iffpicture.lib/ReadAllTexts

   NAME
	ReadAllTexts -- read all TEXT chunks. (V1.0)

   SYNOPSIS
	textList = ReadAllTexts(picture);
	D0                    A0

	struct TextList *ReadAllTexts(struct IFFPicture *);

   FUNCTION
	Reads all TEXT chunks containing text data. Returns a pointer to a
	TextList structure containing count and array pointer into
	IFFPicture's memory, or NULL if not found. Pointers are valid until
	FreeIFFPicture() is called. Library owns the memory - caller must
	NOT free.

	Must be called after ParseIFFPicture(). Metadata is automatically
	read during ParseIFFPicture().

   INPUTS
	picture - pointer to IFFPicture structure.

   RESULT
	textList - pointer to TextList structure containing count and texts
		   array, or NULL if not found.

   SEE ALSO
	ReadText(), ParseIFFPicture(), ReadMetadata(), <iffpicture.h>

